      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 30: Using `remoteMessage.priority` bases the decision on the priority as delivered by FCM, which may be downgraded from the sender-requested priority. That can make an urgent push that was sent as high priority take the lightweight path and skip daemon startup/wake handling while the app is backgrounded. Use `originalPriority` for the semantic decision about whether the push was intended to require full processing.\n\n```suggestion\n        val isHigh \u003d remoteMessage.originalPriority \u003d\u003d RemoteMessage.PRIORITY_HIGH\n```",
